COM Example demonstrating the new study_variable_group design (mzTab-M 2.1)
COM This file shows how to use study variable groups for complex multi-factorial experimental designs

MTD mzTab-version	2.1.0-M
MTD mzTab-ID	EXAMPLE_SV_GROUP_001
MTD title	Multi-factorial design with sex and timepoint factors
MTD description	Example dataset demonstrating the use of study_variable_group for complex experimental designs

COM Study Variable Groups Definition
COM sex group - nominal type (categorical without ordering)
MTD study_variable_group[1]	[,,sex,]
MTD study_variable_group[1]-description	Sex of the individual
MTD study_variable_group[1]-type	[STATO, STATO:0000252, categorical variable]
MTD study_variable_group[1]-datatype	xsd:string

COM timepoint group - ordinal type (ordered categories) with unit
MTD study_variable_group[2]	[,,timepoint,]
MTD study_variable_group[2]-description	Time after treatment in days
MTD study_variable_group[2]-type	[STATO, STATO:0000228, ordinal variable]
MTD study_variable_group[2]-datatype	xsd:integer
MTD study_variable_group[2]-unit	[UO, UO:0000033, day, ]

COM genotype group - categorical type
MTD study_variable_group[3]	[,,genotype, ]
MTD study_variable_group[3]-description	Genetic background of samples
MTD study_variable_group[3]-type	[STATO, STATO:0000252, categorical variable]
MTD study_variable_group[3]-datatype	xsd:string

COM Study Variables Definition
COM Female control at 0 days
MTD study_variable[1]	Female_0day_WT
MTD study_variable[1]-description	Female, wildtype, control timepoint
MTD study_variable[1]-group_ref	study_variable_group[1]
MTD study_variable[1]-assay_refs	assay[1]|assay[2]|assay[3]

